					<p>Za archiv: <persName ref="#ehri_dc_schmiedt_alexander">Alex. Schmiedt</persName>
						<date when="1945-08-11">11. VIII. 1945</date></p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-026_01.png" n="1"/>
					<p>Statement on the <q><placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2793" type="camp">Zossen</placeName>
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-489" type="subject">Baukommando</term></q></p>
					<p>written with <persName ref="#ehri_dc_friedlander_otta">Otto Friedländer</persName>, born <date when="1925-03-14">14. 3. 1925</date>, residing in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName> XIX., <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Sochařská 13</placeName></p>
					<p>On <date when="1944-03-02">2. 3. 1944</date>, I left <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="ghetto">Theresienstadt</placeName> on a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transport</term> with
						200 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">construct</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">buildings</term> in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2793" type="camp">Wulkow near Trebnitz</placeName> on the <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin</placeName>-<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3095057/kostrzyn-nad-odra.html">Küstrin</placeName> line, about 50 km from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin</placeName>. For the
						first three weeks, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> was led by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">SS</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">Obersturmbannführer</term>
						<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000564">Eichmann</persName>, then by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">SS</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">Obersturmführer</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_stuschka_franz">Stuschka</persName>. Also with us were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">SS</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">Unterstürmführer</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_hardenberger">Hardenberger</persName>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">SS</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">Oberscharführers</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_hanke">Hanke</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_dc_stiasny">Stiastni</persName>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">Scharführer</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_proschek">Proschek</persName>, and about 20 <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-437">Waffen</orgName>-<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-437">SS</orgName> as <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1438" type="subject">guards</term>. When we started we had enough <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term>, until about <date when="1944-09">September 1944</date>.
						The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> day for the first 2 months was 12 hours, and then 14 for the entire summer.</p>
					<p>Since <date when="1944-09">September 1944</date> there had been a terrible <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> shortage in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject"
							>camp</term>. We were treated fairly at first, but it gradually worsened. Since fall <date when="1944">1944</date>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">beatings</term> (sticks, rubber batons with metal ends, etc.) were a daily
						occurrence. Favorite sports: squats over a board with nails. In the winter, standing barefoot all night only in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">pants</term> and no <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">shirts</term> in 15 degree below zero weather, standing on <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-818" type="subject">ice</term>, and having cold water poured over us.
						Walking barefoot all day in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-818" type="subject">snow</term>, collecting glass or nails with our mouths, sitting in a 40 x 60 x 80 cm cage after work.</p>
					<p>The excuses they used were limitless. At the end of a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-818" type="subject">freezing</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-818" type="subject">rainy</term>
						<date when="1944-11">November in 1944</date>, for instance, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>, since they had apparently been <q>lazy,</q> had to crawl on their stomachs all over the courtyard and scoop <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-818" type="subject">mud</term> with their bare hands, which took about 4 hours.</p>
					<p>These so-called <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-653" type="subject">punishments</term> are only an example of the rich repertoire of Mr. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">SS</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">Obersturmführer</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_stuschka_franz">Stuschka</persName>.</p>
					<p>The population of the camp peaked in <date when="1944-09">September 1944</date> with about 260 people. In the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-818" type="subject">fall</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-818"
							type="subject">winter</term> about 45 people left on <q><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-653" type="subject">penal</term>
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transports</term></q> to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-847" type="camp">Oranienburg</placeName>, <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName>, or the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-places-place-jmp-49">Small Fortress</placeName>. Only 10 people returned.</p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">Housing</term> conditions: in the beginning, although the temperature fell below zero at night, we slept outside in the woods. Then we slept in wooden <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">shacks</term> that leaked when it <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-818" type="subject">rained</term>. In the summer, the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> spent about 4 months in a 13 x 30 m sandy hole about 8 m deep. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">kitchen</term>, <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">latrine</term>, and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">well</term> were about 1 m away from one another. When this inhuman <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">living situation</term> began to threaten the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-791" type="subject">health</term> of the population and thus the nearby village, the
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-791" type="subject">health</term> committee forbid further <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">living</term> in the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>. We then <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">lived</term> in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837"
							type="subject">houses</term>, of course <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">unheated</term> during the winter.</p>
					<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-280" type="subject">sickroom</term> was the terror of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>. It was a wooden <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">shed</term> (with a 2 cm hole between two planks) without <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">windows</term> and constantly open <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">doors</term>. In January, when it was very <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-818" type="subject">cold</term>, it was about 20 degrees below zero in the <q><term
								ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-280" type="subject">sickroom</term>.</q> The patient wouldn’t get anything to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">eat</term> in the first 3 days (only a watery <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">soup</term>) and then only half a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">portion</term>. These measures were supposed to stop the spread of <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">diseases</term>.</p>
					<p>In <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2793" type="camp">Wulkow</placeName>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">offices</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837"
							type="subject">apartments</term> were being built for the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-427">Reich Security Main Office</orgName> in a remote location hidden in the woods. After the first <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">building</term> was built, the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-427">RSH</orgName>
						<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-427">Amt</orgName> began working under the leadership of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">SS</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">Obergruppenführer</term>
						<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000283">Müller</persName>. The next <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">building</term> was being <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">built</term> and then another, and then several other small <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">buildings</term> (only 3 luxuriously furnished <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">houses</term>) likely for <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-407">party</orgName> leaders, because the <persName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000185">Führer</persName>’s deputy in the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-407">party</orgName>, <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000052"
							>Bohrmann</persName>, visited and toured the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">construction site</term> three times.</p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-026_02.png" n="2"/>
					<p>After the parachutists landed in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3095057/kostrzyn-nad-odra.html">Kostrzyn</placeName> – about <date when="1945-01-28">January 28th, 1945</date> – the Aktenbunkers were blown up and the other documents burned. The <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623" type="subject">evacuated</term> on <date when="1945-02-02">February 2nd, 1945</date>, and we were put on <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">cattle</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">cars</term> about 75 person per car back to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="ghetto">Theresienstadt</placeName>. The journey lasted 8 days with
						provisions that we were told would suffice for 3 days. (Before this, there hadn’t been any <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">bread</term> in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject"
							>camp</term> for about a week). The <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin</placeName>-<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911522/halle-saale.html">Halle</placeName>-<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2805615/wuerzburg.html"
							>Würzburg</placeName>-<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2861650/nuernberg.html">Norimberg</placeName>-<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName> journey was approx. 1,000 km long.</p>
					<p>The <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2837549/schnarchenreuth.html">Schnarchenreuth</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> near <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2902768/hof.html">Hof</placeName> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2951839/bavaria.html">Bavaria</placeName> (from <date
							when="1944-03-13">March 13th, 1944</date> to <date when="1945-04-22">April 22nd, 1945</date>) had the same guards and same conditions as <q><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-489" type="subject">Baukommando</term>
							<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2793" type="camp">Zossen</placeName>.</q> During the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623" type="subject">evacuation</term>, the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-489" type="subject">Baukommando</term>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2902768/hof.html">Hof</placeName> returned on foot in 8 days via <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2929226/ore-mountains.html">Krušné Hory</placeName>-<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3073803/karlovy-vary.html">Karlovy
							Vary</placeName>-<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3077685/chomutov.html">Chomutov</placeName> (280 km) to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="ghetto">Theresienstadt</placeName>.</p>
					<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>, on <date when="1945-08-10">August 10th, 1945</date></p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_friedlander_otta">Otto Friedländer</persName></p>
					<p>Statement accepted by:</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_kratkova_marta">Marta Kratková</persName></p>
					<p>Signature of witnesses:</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_weinberger_robert">Robert Weinberger</persName></p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_shek_alisa">Alice Ehrmannová</persName></p>
